The Library System is a backend application that allows users to manage books, borrow and return them, and leave reviews. It includes features like user authentication, book management, and a review system.

## Cloning the Repository
1. **Clone the Repository:**
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/library-system.git

    cd library-system
    bundle install
2.**Set Up the Database:**
  rails db:create
  rails db:migrate

3.**Run the Rails server:**


**How to Use the Application**
**User Registration**
Register a New User:
Send a POST request to /api/v1/users with the following JSON body:
{
  "user": {
    "email": "user@example.com",
    "password": "password",
    "password_confirmation": "password"
  }
}

**Book Management**
List All Books:
Send a GET request to /api/v1/books.

Create a New Book:
Send a POST request to /api/v1/books with the book details in the JSON body.

Update a Book:

Send a PATCH request to /api/v1/books/:id with the updated book details.

Delete a Book:

Send a DELETE request to /api/v1/books/:id.

**Borrowing and Returning Books**
Borrow a Book:

Send a POST request to /api/v1/borrowings with the book ID and user ID.


Borrowing and Returning Books
Borrow a Book:

Send a POST request to /api/v1/borrowings with the book ID and user ID.


**Reviews and Ratings**
List All Reviews:

Send a GET request to /api/v1/reviews.

Create a Review:

Send a POST request to /api/v1/reviews with the review details in the JSON body.

Update a Review:

Send a PATCH request to /api/v1/reviews/:id with the updated review details.

Delete a Review:

Send a DELETE request to /api/v1/reviews/:id.





